<table border="0">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
<p>The Fall 2011 conference marked the 10th anniversary of the PPC and was the best attended to date. The event was hosted by the BYU-Idaho English Academic Society, and Alpha Delta Phi Chapter of the Pi Sigma Alpha National Honor Society for Political Science.</p>
<p>Gary Schmidt, a prolific writer of children's books and young adult novels, and professor of English at Calvin College, was the Keynote Speaker for the English section of the conference.</p>
<p>In the Political Science section, Robin Riggs, Executive VP for Government Affairs and General Counsel, appeared alongside Willy Fautre, Director of Human Rights without Frontiers International, as Keynote Speakers.</p>
<p><em>(<a href="Documents/english/PPC 2012/Day Program for PPC_2011.pdf" target="_blank">Click image to view the 2011 PPC program</a>)</em></p>
